


Harbinger Capital Partners












About Us
Our History


About Us
Harbinger Capital Partners is a private investment firm specializing in event/distressed strategies. Founded in 2001 with Philip Falcone as the Chief Investment Officer, Harbinger Capital Partners seeks to invest in alpha-generating ideas that are uncorrelated to investment cycles.
Harbinger seeks investments that typically fall into the following four categories: 

Event – investments in companies where the Harbinger team identifies a significant opportunity to actively engage with a company to unlock value;
Distressed/Bankruptcy – investments in companies that are already in default, in bankruptcy, or in some other stage of financial failure or distress;
Value – passive investments in securities where Harbinger believes a positive catalyst for value realization is already present; and
Corporate Shorts – passive investments where Harbinger views the security to be overvalued or believes weakening fundamental trends or identifiable negative catalysts are apparent.

Philip Falcone leads Harbinger's investment team, relying on his extensive experience in distressed debt, leveraged finance, and special situations across an array of market cycles.

©  Harbinger Capital Partners. All Rights Reserved.   |   PRIVACY POLICY









Harbinger Capital Partners












About Us
Our History


Our History
In 2001, Philip Falcone capitalized on the significant opportunities within the distressed marketplace and became the Chief Investment Officer of Harbinger Capital Partners upon its inception. Through conviction in his ability to identify value in credit/distressed, Mr. Falcone led an investment team focused on opportunities in credit. 
Over the next few years, as the distressed credit market subsided and the broader investment universe became more sophisticated, Harbinger adjusted its strategy accordingly and, as most investment firms focused upon distressed opportunities do, evolved into special situation and event strategies as well. With extensive experience in several different strategies, Harbinger was able to respond to market fluctuations over time with rigor, efficiency and built-in flexibility. As Harbinger reached a critical mass, it was able to engage proactively with companies in order to enhance value. 
Although Harbinger's expansion since its inception has been substantial, the underlying work ethic and conviction to succeed, the principles on which the company was started, continue to define Harbinger Capital Partners today.

©  Harbinger Capital Partners. All Rights Reserved.   |   PRIVACY POLICY









